## Mental Models
- First principles thinking (from engineering background)
- "Demos over memos" — showing beats telling
- AI should scale human creativity, not replace it
- The bottleneck is adoption, not technology
- Meet people where they already work
- Layered thinking — breaks problems into categories and buckets
- Remove enterprise constraints to find what's possible, then bring it back inside (personal tinkering → work ideas)
- Push → pull as a maturity signal — success is when people come to you instead of you going to them
- Creative taste as moat — human judgment and cultural fluency are what make a team irreplaceable by AI
- Systems that work without you explaining them = the real measure of success
- Small tests before full commitment — run one agent with one team, see what happens
- Don't self-certify your own numbers — get independent validation
- Backchannel to pressure-test, not to get permission
- People readiness is harder to assess than tech readiness — probe longer on the human side

